'''''Anakin: Apprentice''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] young readers book written by [[Marc Cerasini]] and illustrated by [[Tommy Lee Edwards]]. The book is part of the ''[[Jedi Readers]]'' series, and it was published by [[LucasBooks]] on [[April 23]], [[2002]].

Set immediately before [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']], ''Anakin: Apprentice'' follows [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] as he reflects on his past adventures.

==Publisher's summary==
''Nineteen-year-old Anakin Skywalker, apprentice to Obi-Wan Kenobi, remembers some of his past adventures in which he raced swoop bikes, built androids, and found crystals to complete his lightsaber''.

==Plot summary==
{{Plot|adaptation}}

==Continuity==
''Anakin: Apprentice'' adapts events from other ''[[Star Wars]]'' books, including ''[[Jedi Quest: Path to Truth]]'' and ''[[Rogue Planet]]''.

